               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-xxx: Prayer of Our Lady Mary at Golgotha, Säne Golǝgota, ጸሎተ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘሰኔ፡ ጎልጎታ፡. Copied and printed several times in its Gə‘əz and Amharic versions, e.g., ጸሎተ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘሰኔ፡ ጎልጎታ፡ በመቃብረ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡  (Addis Ababa: Täsfa, 1949 E.C.); ጸሎተ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘሰኔ፡ ጎልጎታ፡ (Addis Ababa: Täsfa, 1963 E.C.); see also Grébaut, “La prière de Marie au Golgotha,” and Basset, Apocryphes 5 30 –47; StrLin 47, <locus target="#73r"/>; EMML 1213, <locus target="#1a"/>.  f<locus target="#31r"/>-41v: Table blessing, Table Prayer, “We beseech you,” Sä’alnakä, ሰአልናከ፡, MD 634ff.  F<locus target="#42r"/>-xxx: Asmat prayer against wild animals, ጸሎት: በእንተ: መስተሃድር:. F. ii v: illumination of the martyrdom of Saint Sebastian. F<locus target="#45rv"/>: Asmat Prayer against the demon Buda. F<locus target="#1r"/> and passim mention the owners, ሎሚ ማርያማዊት and ወልደ ማርያም. A later owner has also added the name, ወልደ ዮና. <locus target="#44v"/>: Historical note in blue ink: On Sane 23, 1895, the church of Addis Alem was consecrated.</summary>
